## Step 2 — Replace songs.js entirely

Replace the 3 fake songs with real metadata. Add a `stems` array per song (each entry: `{ id, label, file, color, icon }`). The `file` field is the clean filename under `audio/<slug>/`. Remove `synthKey`; keep `bpm`, `timeSignature`, `barDuration`. Keep `sections` and `cues` with BPM-derived approximate timestamps (demo quality is fine).

**He Will Hold Me Fast — 96 BPM, key A, barDuration = 2.5s**
- Estimated duration: 300s (5 min typical worship song)
- Sections (8-bar blocks = 20s each, rough): Intro 0s, Verse 0→20s, Pre-C ~40s, Chorus ~60s, Verse2 ~100s, Pre-C2 ~140s, Chorus2 ~160s, Bridge ~200s, Tag/Outro ~260s
- 8 stems

**Greater Than Great — 97 BPM, key G, barDuration = 2.474s**
- Estimated duration: 280s
- 7 stems (no vocals stem; use backing for full mix reference)

**What a Generous God — 114 BPM, key D, barDuration = 2.105s**
- Estimated duration: 320s
- 10 stems

Replace STEM_CONFIG with a note that it is now per-song (rendered from `song.stems`). The `SONGS` array drives everything; the global STEM_CONFIG is no longer needed (or keep it as a fallback display-order hint).

---

## Step 3 — Refactor AudioEngine.loadSong

Replace the `renderers` array (which calls synthetic render functions) with a fetch loop over `song.stems`:

```js
// pseudocode — replaces lines ~283-317 of AudioEngine.js
const BASE = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;  // '/demos/audio-software-engineer-needed-for/'

for (const stemDef of song.stems) {
  const url = `${BASE}audio/${song.slug}/${stemDef.file}`;
  const resp = await fetch(url);
  const arrayBuffer = await resp.arrayBuffer();
  const buffer = await this.ctx.decodeAudioData(arrayBuffer);
  this.stems[stemDef.id] = {
    buffer,
    volume: 80,
    muted: false,
    soloed: false,
    source: null,
    volumeGain: ...,   // same GainNode setup as before
    muteGain: ...,
    panner: ...,
  };
  if (onProgress) onProgress(done++ / song.stems.length);
}
```

Keep `schedClickTick` (used by countIn/metronome if present). Remove `renderDrums`, `renderBass`, `renderKeys`, `renderPads`, `renderClick`, `renderGuide` — they are only called from the old `renderers` array and are no longer needed. Keep ROOT_HZ only if still referenced elsewhere; otherwise remove.

The `playSong` / `stopSong` / `setVolume` / `setMute` / `setSolo` methods need zero changes — they operate on `this.stems` which has the same shape.

