- produced: planner3.out — complete action plan with exact file mappings, AudioEngine refactor spec, and build/deploy steps; no unknowns remain
- decisions: use MP3 stems for all 3 songs (GTG uses greater-than-great-mp3/ folder, not WAV); clean filenames with no spaces; per-song `stems` array in songs.js replaces global STEM_CONFIG; fetch/decodeAudioData replaces all synth render functions; keep schedClickTick only
- next needs: demo-builder executes the 5 steps above — copy stems, edit songs.js, edit AudioEngine.js, edit UI component, rebuild, deploy; commit first as user requested
- risks: bundle size may be large (25 MP3 files, potentially 50-200MB total) — GH Pages has no hard size limit per file but initial load will be slow; mitigate by loading stems only when song is selected (lazy load); Vite may warn about large assets in public/ (not a build error, just a warning); `Organ&Synths` filename has `&` — must quote shell path correctly
